10.Merge two lists.

1st approach-->l + l1 → simplest, creates a new list.
l = [1,2,3,4] 
l1=[5,6,7,8]
print(l+l1)
o/p-->[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]

tc=O(n + m)
sc=O(n + m)



2nd approach-->extend() → modifies the existing list.
l = [1, 2, 3, 4]
l1 = [5, 6, 7, 8]
l.extend(l1)
print(l)
TC: O(m)
SC: O(1)



3rd approach-->
l = [1,2,3,4] 
l1=[5,6,7,8]
res=[]

for num in l:
    res.append(num)

for num in l1:
    res.append(num)
     print(res)
TC: O(n + m)
SC: O(n + m)

